40|$|The PREDESS model (Previsions Regionales de l'Economie et de la Demande d'Energie par Source et par Secteur) {{analyzes}} {{the economies of}} the developing countries by region and sector. It integrates the dissymmetry {{of the world economy}} into the productive process, with the industrialized countries acting as the traditional driving force. An energy model, also constructed by region and sector, is linked to the world economic model. It includes both commercial and <b>traditional</b> <b>energy</b> <b>sources</b> and stresses their development and substitution possibilities. The model pays special attention to the problems of <b>traditional</b> <b>energy</b> <b>sources</b> (such as deforestation) and {{analyzes the}} consequences of replacing traditional with commercial sources. ...|$|R
